*** Databases Languages

1. DDL - Data Definition Language
2. DML - Data Manipulation Language
3. DCL - Data Control Language
4. TCL - Transaction Control Language

DDL
- CREATE
- ALTER - Changes Data
- DROP - Delete Schema
- TRUNCATE - Delete records
- RENAME
- COMMENT

DML
- SELECT
- INSERT
- UPDATE
- DELETE
- MERGE - UPSERT( update and insert )
- CALL - PL/SQL
- LOCK TABLE - Concurrency control
	- multiple users performaing CRUD over a single resource is called as concurrency

DCL
- GRANT - permission(INSERT, SELECT..)
- REVOKE - permission(INSERT, SELECT..)

TCL
- rollback - undo change
- commit - save change
- save point - temp save change

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

*** 3 Tier Architecture

External Layer	
	^
	|
Concetual Layer	
	^
	|
Physical Layer


all layers are inter-related and independent

Physical layer - how data is stored - location
Concetual Layer	- What data is stored - (name, age, etc..)
External Layer - View of data

change in any layer should not effect other